        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 2: Vague service descriptions</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Homepage says "HVAC Services" or "Complete Heating & Cooling Solutions." Homeowner doesn't know if you handle their specific problem. <strong>Fix:</strong> List specific services with icons: "AC Repair, Installation, Maintenance, Furnace Service, Duct Cleaning, Indoor Air Quality." Results: 4x more qualified calls. Clear services = you fix my issue = quote request.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 3: No maintenance plan promoted</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Contractor offers annual maintenance but never highlights it online. Homeowner doesn't know = no recurring revenue. <strong>Fix:</strong> Create dedicated page: "Annual Maintenance: $149/year - 2 Visits, Priority Service, 15% Off Repairs." Show benefits clearly. Results: 53% more plan signups. Visible plans = recurring revenue.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 4: Credentials not displayed</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">"Fully Licensed & Insured" buried or missing. Homeowner searches for contractors = sees unprofessional site = worries about scams = calls competitor. <strong>Fix:</strong> Add "Licensed & Insured - License #XYZ" badge prominently near header. Results: 47% more qualified calls, fewer legitimacy questions. Credentials visible = trust = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 5: Non-existent "Request Quote" form</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Contractor has quote form but it's broken, loads slowly, or asks for too much info. Homeowner gives up = calls competitor. <strong>Fix:</strong> Simple 3-field form (name, phone, problem). Test it weekly. Auto-respond within 2 hours. Results: One contractor went from 8 to 47 quote requests/month after fixing form. Working form = leads.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-red-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-white rounded-r">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Mistake 6: Poor mobile experience</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">83% of HVAC searches happen on phones (emergencies). Tiny text, unclickable buttons, phone number not clickable. <strong>Fix:</strong> Mobile-first design. Test on your phone. Click-to-call button always visible. Large buttons (thumb-friendly). Results: One contractor went from 31% to 83% mobile call-through after optimization. Mobile = emergency calls.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

